---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lang = 'en';
---

<BaseLayout title="Contributor Template | Ayamatma" description="The filter every article must pass through before writing begins." lang={lang}>
  <section class="section stack">
    <h1 class="section-title">Contributor Template</h1>
    <p class="muted">Lekhana-Vidhi · The Writing Protocol</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="prose template-intro">
      <p class="lead">Every article must pass through this filter before writing begins.</p>
      <p>
        This template applies to all contributors—including us. It operationalizes the
        <a href="/manifesto">Five Protocols</a> into a concrete workflow. No article proceeds
        to draft until these six fields are answered with precision.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="template-form">
      <div class="template-field">
        <div class="field-header">
          <span class="field-number">1</span>
          <h3 class="field-title">Title</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="field-instruction">Clear, descriptive, non-clickbait.</p>
        <p class="field-example">
          <strong>Good:</strong> "The Translation Trap: Why Ātman is Not 'Soul' or 'Self'"<br>
          <strong>Bad:</strong> "The Secret Ancient Indians Knew About Your Soul!"
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="template-field">
        <div class="field-header">
          <span class="field-number">2</span>
          <h3 class="field-title">Sanskrit Key Terms</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="field-instruction">List 3-5 core terms to be defined or explored.</p>
        <p class="field-example">
          <strong>Example:</strong> Ātman, Jīva, Sākṣī, Ahaṅkāra, Dṛk-Dṛśya
        </p>
        <p class="field-note">
          Per <em>Protocol III (Language)</em>: These terms must be defined with etymological
          precision using their <em>dhātu</em> roots. No vague translations.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="template-field">
        <div class="field-header">
          <span class="field-number">3</span>
          <h3 class="field-title">The Target Fallacy</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="field-instruction">What specific misunderstanding or "spiritual fluff" does this article correct?</p>
        <p class="field-example">
          <strong>Example:</strong> "The conflation of Ātman with the Western metaphysical 'Soul'
          imports creationist, individualist, and localized attributes that the Upaniṣads explicitly deny."
        </p>
        <p class="field-note">
          Every article must have a clear adversary—a misconception to dismantle.
          If there is no fallacy to correct, the article is mere commentary, not inquiry.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="template-field">
        <div class="field-header">
          <span class="field-number">4</span>
          <h3 class="field-title">The Scientific Model</h3>
          <span class="field-optional">(if applicable)</span>
        </div>
        <p class="field-instruction">Which specific framework is used as the analogy?</p>
        <p class="field-example">
          <strong>Example:</strong> "Thermodynamic entropy as an analogy for <em>Māyā</em>'s
          tendency toward differentiation."
        </p>
        <p class="field-warning">
          <strong>Warning per Protocol II:</strong> This is a <em>dṛṣṭānta</em> (pedagogical illustration),
          not empirical proof. State this explicitly in the article. No quantum mysticism.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="template-field">
        <div class="field-header">
          <span class="field-number">5</span>
          <h3 class="field-title">The Steel Man</h3>
          <span class="field-sanskrit">Pūrvapakṣa</span>
        </div>
        <p class="field-instruction">What is the strongest counter-argument to your thesis?</p>
        <p class="field-example">
          <strong>Example:</strong> "A Dvaitin would argue that the distinction between Jīva and
          Ātman is real and eternal, citing Madhva's commentary on Brahma Sūtra 1.1.1, where..."
        </p>
        <p class="field-note">
          Per <em>Protocol IV (Argument)</em>: You must state the opposing view so well that
          its proponent would say "Yes, that is exactly what I mean." Only then may you refute.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="template-field">
        <div class="field-header">
          <span class="field-number">6</span>
          <h3 class="field-title">The Experiential Anchor</h3>
          <span class="field-sanskrit">Anubhava-Sūtra</span>
        </div>
        <p class="field-instruction">How does this intellectual concept translate into actual practice or change?</p>
        <p class="field-example">
          <strong>Example:</strong> "The practitioner, having understood that Ātman is not the
          psychological 'self,' can now sit in meditation without trying to 'improve' or 'fix'
          the witnessed thoughts. The instruction shifts from 'calm your mind' to 'notice who is watching.'"
        </p>
        <p class="field-note">
          Per <em>Protocol V (Experience)</em>: Intellectual understanding is entry fee.
          Every article must point toward <em>aparokṣa</em> (direct) verification.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="template-summary">
      <h2>Before You Write</h2>
      <p>Complete this template. If any field is blank or vague, the article is not ready.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Title: <em>___</em></li>
        <li>Sanskrit Terms: <em>___</em></li>
        <li>Target Fallacy: <em>___</em></li>
        <li>Scientific Model: <em>___ (or N/A)</em></li>
        <li>Steel Man: <em>___</em></li>
        <li>Experiential Anchor: <em>___</em></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="quote-block">
      <p class="sanskrit">यथा खनन् खनित्रेण नरो वार्यधिगच्छति</p>
      <p class="english">As a man digging with a spade reaches water, so a student through inquiry reaches truth.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="margin-top: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.85rem;">— Śaṅkara, Vivekacūḍāmaṇi</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .template-intro .lead {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .template-form {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .template-field {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    border: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 1.75rem 2rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .template-field::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 2px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--accent-warm), var(--accent-cool));
    border-radius: 16px 16px 0 0;
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .field-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .field-number {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .field-title {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .field-optional {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-left: 0.5rem;
  }

  .field-sanskrit {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent-cool);
    margin-left: 0.5rem;
  }

  .field-instruction {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-soft);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .field-example {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    background: var(--bg-section);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .field-note {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--accent-cool);
    padding-left: 1rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .field-warning {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    background: var(--accent-warm-soft);
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .template-summary {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    border: 2px dashed var(--border);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .template-summary h2 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .template-summary p {
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .template-summary ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    text-align: left;
    max-width: 400px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .template-summary li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--border);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-soft);
  }

  .template-summary li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .template-field {
      padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    }

    .field-header {
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }
  }
</style>
